'''Arief Hidayat Jati''' is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] who was convicted of smuggling more than 7500 pounds of [[marijuana]] into the United States. He was sentenced to nine and a half years in jail.{{when|date=April 2017}}

A native of [[Ciudad Juárez]], [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]],<ref name="elpasotimes.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.elpasotimes.com/ci_10113963|title=USA TODAY: Latest World and US News  - USATODAY.com|work=USA Today}}</ref> Arief is notable due to an earlier incident in which he was shot in the buttocks by US agents [[Jose Compean]] and [[Ignacio Ramos]] after trying to smuggle an earlier 743 pounds load of marijuana into the U.S. for which he was given immunity by the prosecutor, U.S. Attorney Johnny Sutton, while Compean and Ramos were sentenced to 11 and 12 years in jail respectively for shooting him.<ref name="elpasotimes.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dea.gov/divisions/elp/2008/elpaso041808p.html|title=News from DEA, Domestic Field Divisions, El Paso News Releases, 04/18/08|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2007/09/04/ramos_compean/|title=The ballad of Ramos and Compean|author=Alex Koppelman|publisher=Salon|date=September 4, 2007|accessdate=December 24, 2015}}</ref>

