'''Samir Abi Rashed''' (in [[Arabic]] {{lang|ar|سمير ابي راشد}}), born in Beirut in 1947,<ref>{{cite web|title=Samir Abi Rached|publisher=One Fine Art|url=http://onefineart.com/en/artists/samir-abi-rached/|accessdate=August 26, 2011}}</ref> is a [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] [[Painting|painter]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Simarski|first=Lynn Teo|title=Keepers of Lebanon's Light|date=February 1989|publisher=Saudi Aramco World|url=http://www.saudiaramcoworld.com/issue/198902/keepers.of.lebanon.s.light.htm|accessdate=August 26, 2011}}</ref> His work is representative<ref>{{cite web|title=لوحات سمير ابي راشد رسالة انسانية منقذة|publisher=Al-Khayma|url=http://www.al-khayma.com/culture/samirabirashed_09052011.htm|accessdate=August 26, 2011|date=May 9, 2011|language=Arabic}}</ref> of the influence of surrealism on middle eastern painters and expresses, with a careful and almost "photographic"<ref>{{cite web|title=Lebanon|publisher=Microsoft Encarta|url=http://acc.teachmideast.org/map.php?module_id=4&country_id=10|year=2010|accessdate=August 26, 2011}}</ref> technical execution, an erotic unconscious world of dreams and symbols.<ref>{{citation|title=Consultation collective sur les problèmes contemporains des arts arabes dans leurs relations socio-culturelles avec le monde arabe|publisher=Unesco|date=December 1973|url=http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0000/000063/006362fb.pdf|accessdate=August 26, 2011|page=11|language=French}}</ref><ref name="Nahed Hakim2010">{{cite book|last=Nahed Hakim|first=Samar |title=L'imaginaire dans l'art et la poésie au Liban|year=2010|publisher=Harmattan|isbn=978-2-296-11255-1|pages=91, 108, 125, 126}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Exposition collective à l'occasion du 125ème anniversaire de la fondation du "Collège de la sagesse" |publisher=Art et Culture|url=http://www.rdl.com.lb/2000/3742/art1.html|accessdate=August 26, 2011|language=French}}</ref>

