{{Infobox person | name = Zuzana Števulová | image = Zuzana Števulová of Slovakia Director of the Human Rights League.jpg | image_size = | caption = in Washington in 2016 | birth_name = | birth_date = 1984 | birth_place = [[Slovakia]] | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | other_names = | known_for = human rights campaigner | education = | employer = | occupation = | party = | footnotes = | nationality = [[Slovakia]] }} '''Zuzana Števulová''' (born 1984) is a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] lawyer, lecturer and activist who assists [[Immigration to Europe|migrants]]. She was the first Slovak to be given an [[International Women of Courage Award]].
==Life== Števulová was born in [[Slovakia]] in 1984. She is lecturer at the [[University of Trnava]] in Slovakia. She helped create the Integration Policy for the Slovak Republic.<ref>[http://migrationonline.cz/en/about-us/our-team/stevulova-zuzana Zuzana Stevulova], migrationonline.cz, Retrieved 15 July 2016</ref>
She had campaigned for the rights of refugees and migrants arriving in Europe and in 2016 she was the first Slovak to be given an [[International Women of Courage Award]] in Washington DC.<ref>[http://www.hrl.sk/en/news/zuzana-stevulova-receives-international-women-courage-award Zuzana Števulová receives International Women of Courage Award], Human Rights League of Slovakia, Retrieved 15 July 2016</ref> She has won important cases to overturn refusals in Slovakia to grant [[political asylum]] and to support the rights of the migrants in her country.<ref>[https://www.state.gov/s/gwi/programs/iwoc/2016/bio/ Biographies], State.gov, Retrieved 15 July 2016</ref>
